		<td><b>Famicom audio correction</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Looks like I previously counted pins wrong and the Famicom cart audio is at least partially connected correctly.  Pins 45 and 46 ARE connected to each other on the board, and that line is blended with the audio output.  It is also connected to EXP 9 on the NES slot.  CIRAM /CE connected to ground is still correct.  I have no Famicom games so I dont know what else I can look at on the slot.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


