	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />To be honest, I don't like the idea of replacing the NES and Famicom controller ports with USB ports, as that would rule out the use of any NES peripherials for which USB adapters do not exist.  That basically means the only peripherial that would work would be NES controllers.  No Family Basic Keyboard, ROB, etc.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
